Two traffic police officers were on Friday arrested by anti-corruption detectives near Nyeri town on the Othaya - Nyeri road.Central region Ethics and Anti-Corruption Commission deputy director Jackson Mue said the officers attached to Nyeri Central traffic base were arrested after graft allegations of soliciting bribes from motorists.The early morning incident attracted members of the public, who said the officers had been collecting bribes from motorists, mostly PSVs and boda boda operators, for long. They praised the EACC. One of the detectives in civilian clothes was injured after his finger was bitten during the commotion of trying the arrest the two men. He was taken to a nearby health facility for treatment.